<i>K. SPARKS:
♪ Yeah, I’m everywhere ♪</i>

10:21.621 --> 10:23.121
<i>♪</i>

10:23.248 --> 10:24.048
<i>♪ You ain’t never there ♪</i>

10:24.124 --> 10:26.334
<i>♪</i>

10:26.459 --> 10:28.089
<i>♪ Yeah, I’m everywhere ♪</i>

10:28.169 --> 10:30.469
[ panting ]

10:30.547 --> 10:33.097
<i>K. SPARKS:
♪ Yeah, I’m everywhere ♪</i>

10:33.174 --> 10:35.554
<i>♪ Yeah, I’m everywhere ♪</i>

10:35.635 --> 10:37.475
You gonna tell me
who shot you?

10:37.554 --> 10:40.724
I mean, I don’t know which one
of the motherfuckers shot me.

10:40.807 --> 10:42.357
It was‐‐
[ winces ]

10:42.475 --> 10:44.145
It was a lot
of them shooting.

10:44.227 --> 10:46.397
All I know is,
it was a Serbian nigga.

10:46.479 --> 10:48.649
You said nothing
was gonna happen to you.

10:48.731 --> 10:51.271
Now you have a big hole
in your shoulder,

10:51.359 --> 10:53.819
and I’m not sticking around
to watch you get killed.

10:54.946 --> 10:57.196
Time’s up, Dre.

10:57.323 --> 11:01.323
I am packing my shit
and the baby’s shit,

11:01.411 --> 11:03.531
and we’re getting on a plane
to Vegas tonight.

11:03.663 --> 11:06.083
You out your fucking mind.

11:06.166 --> 11:08.256
You ain’t taking Heaven
from me.

11:08.334 --> 11:11.874
No one is taking Heaven
from me.

11:12.005 --> 11:13.835
You understand me?

11:13.965 --> 11:15.385
Come with us, then.

11:16.843 --> 11:20.013
You, me, Heaven...

11:20.096 --> 11:22.686
let’s start over
as a family.

11:23.850 --> 11:25.190
You got lucky today.

11:25.268 --> 11:26.648
12 inches to the right,

11:26.728 --> 11:29.108
and you would have
a bullet in the heart.

11:29.189 --> 11:30.859
You can’t talk your way
out of that one.

11:30.982 --> 11:33.022
[ dark music ]

11:33.151 --> 11:35.061
Let’s just go, Dre.

11:36.529 --> 11:38.989
What’s left here for us?

11:39.073 --> 11:42.033
<i>♪</i>

11:42.118 --> 11:44.328
Okay, okay.

11:44.412 --> 11:45.532
[ breathes raggedly ]

11:45.663 --> 11:48.873
[ smooches ]
Okay, okay.

11:48.958 --> 11:51.048
There ain’t nothing left.

11:51.169 --> 11:54.089
You’re right.
L‐let’s‐let’s do it.

11:54.214 --> 11:55.584
Let’s get the fuck out of here.

11:55.715 --> 11:57.215
‐ [ laughs ]
‐ Okay.

11:57.300 --> 11:59.140
<i>♪</i>

11:59.219 --> 12:00.679
Okay.

12:00.762 --> 12:03.132
<i>♪</i>

12:03.223 --> 12:04.643
‐ I’m going to start packing.
‐ Okay.

12:04.724 --> 12:07.394
I just...I just need
some, uh, traveling money.

12:07.518 --> 12:08.688
But you have some
of that saved, right?

12:08.770 --> 12:10.400
I was supposed to step
into some cash,

12:10.480 --> 12:11.940
but shit got fucked up today.

12:12.065 --> 12:13.395
<i>HEAVEN:
Mommy!</i>

12:13.524 --> 12:15.904
‐ Shit.
‐ But no, look, look, look.

12:16.027 --> 12:17.407
I’ma handle that.

12:17.528 --> 12:19.238
I’ma take care of y’all.

12:19.322 --> 12:21.152
You’re gonna hate this,

12:21.241 --> 12:24.571
but, um...

12:24.702 --> 12:26.122
you know where you have to go.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.836
Hell no.

12:28.915 --> 12:30.245
No.

12:30.375 --> 12:31.755
I’m never going back there.

12:31.876 --> 12:33.376
<i>♪</i>

12:33.461 --> 12:35.581
Do you have a better idea?

12:35.672 --> 12:38.592
<i>♪</i>

12:40.551 --> 12:42.511
Does it bother you?

12:42.595 --> 12:44.685
Locking niggas up
who look like you,

12:44.764 --> 12:46.804
hoping they turn on each other?

12:46.933 --> 12:48.433
<i>My bad, though.</i>

12:48.559 --> 12:51.359
Prison‐industrial complex
ain’t about race.

12:51.437 --> 12:52.737
It’s about class.

12:52.814 --> 12:54.604
Oh!

12:54.691 --> 12:57.151
So you an enlightened
motherfucker, huh?

12:57.277 --> 13:00.077
Either way,
you still sitting in here.

13:00.154 --> 13:01.864
The next move’s on you.

13:01.948 --> 13:04.498
I’m a grown‐ass man, <i>mami.
</i> I can take it.

13:04.617 --> 13:08.127
According to your file,
you already have two strikes.

13:08.204 --> 13:11.494
Let’s see...
felony assault.

13:11.624 --> 13:14.124
Dude was twice my size,
came at me with a bottle,

13:14.252 --> 13:15.832
and I catch a charge?

13:15.962 --> 13:17.002
Felony larceny?

13:17.130 --> 13:18.970
Okay, I did that shit,

13:19.090 --> 13:21.640
but them stereos
were just sitting
on the back of that truck.

13:21.718 --> 13:23.308
It’s just like entrapment
or something.

13:23.386 --> 13:25.096
With the amount of weight
in that warehouse,

13:25.179 --> 13:27.479
you’re looking
at 15 to 30 years.

13:27.557 --> 13:29.897
Maybe somebody ratted us out,

13:29.976 --> 13:32.646
but our judicial system
allows you to lie.

13:32.770 --> 13:35.180
You heard of the persistent
felony offender statute?

13:35.315 --> 13:36.985
<i>Third strike and you get life.</i>

13:37.066 --> 13:39.906
This new charge?
It’s your third strike.

13:39.986 --> 13:43.326
So unless you wanna spend
the rest of your life
in an orange jumpsuit...

13:43.448 --> 13:44.788
[ suspenseful music ]

13:44.866 --> 13:46.656
You need to give me something
on Tommy Egan.

13:46.743 --> 13:48.533
‐ Tommy who?
<i>‐ You know what I love</i>

13:48.661 --> 13:50.571
about criminals?

13:50.663 --> 13:52.583
They’re predictable as fuck.

13:52.665 --> 13:54.505
Look, you know
I don’t wanna do life,

13:54.625 --> 13:55.875
but I ain’t no snitch.

13:56.002 --> 13:57.162
I ain’t no snitch.

13:57.295 --> 14:00.085
I can’t tell you
who gave us the tip,

14:00.173 --> 14:03.383
but just think about who knew
about the warehouse.

14:03.509 --> 14:06.179
Then think about who wasn’t
in there that day.

14:06.262 --> 14:08.432
[ chuckles ] Does this shit
actually work on niggas?

14:08.514 --> 14:10.264
I can’t talk.

14:10.350 --> 14:13.820
If I do, I’m as good as dead
as soon as I hit the street.

14:13.895 --> 14:16.355
You a little man
with one big, tough friend.

14:16.481 --> 14:18.191
The minute 2‐Bit
gets transferred

14:18.316 --> 14:19.856
to another block,
you straight food.

14:19.984 --> 14:22.574
‐ [ laughs ]
<i>‐ What’s that gonna be like,</i>

14:22.695 --> 14:25.365
day in and day out,

14:25.490 --> 14:28.460
being tossed around for sport?

14:28.534 --> 14:31.994
<i>You really gonna do a life bid
for Tommy Egan,</i>

14:32.080 --> 14:35.920
under those conditions,
no possibility of parole,

14:36.042 --> 14:38.622
no end in sight?

14:38.711 --> 14:41.041
I stood by that motherfucker
through all kinds of crazy shit.

14:41.172 --> 14:43.172
When’s the last time
that motherfucker stood by you?

14:43.257 --> 14:45.097
<i>♪</i>

14:45.218 --> 14:46.968
If Tommy dimed you out,

14:47.053 --> 14:48.973
<i>he’s taking money
out of your mouth,</i>

14:49.055 --> 14:51.475
out of the mouths
of your loved ones.

14:51.557 --> 14:53.767
He sentenced you
to die in here.

14:53.893 --> 14:56.563
I’m predictable, remember?

14:56.646 --> 14:58.186
Guess what I say next.

14:59.273 --> 15:00.193
Lawyer.

15:00.274 --> 15:02.404
<i>♪</i>

15:02.527 --> 15:03.817
You should look
into the murder

15:03.903 --> 15:05.443
of a dealer named Poncho.

15:05.571 --> 15:06.901
<i>♪</i>

15:07.031 --> 15:10.951
<i>CHOIR:
♪ He is my friend ♪</i>

15:11.077 --> 15:13.877
<i>MAN: ♪ Oh ♪</i>

15:13.955 --> 15:16.955
<i>CHOIR:
♪ Through thick and thin... ♪</i>

15:17.083 --> 15:20.043
[ dark music ]

15:20.128 --> 15:21.508
‐ Mom.
‐ [ gasps ]

15:21.587 --> 15:22.927
I‐I‐I don’t have much money.

15:23.047 --> 15:24.927
You can take what I have.
Don’t hurt me.

15:25.049 --> 15:27.849
It’s me. It’s me. It’s me.
It’s Andre.

15:27.927 --> 15:30.267
[ laughs ]

15:30.346 --> 15:32.306
What do you want?

15:32.432 --> 15:34.092
‐ Mama, I‐‐
‐ Don’t you "Mama" me.

15:34.183 --> 15:38.393
You’ve got some nerve
just walking up
after all these years.

15:38.479 --> 15:41.029
No calls, no letters, no email.

15:41.107 --> 15:44.197
For all I knew,
you could’ve been dead.

15:44.277 --> 15:46.367
Mama, I didn’t reach out
’cause I didn’t think
you wanted to see me.

15:46.446 --> 15:49.326
You’re my son.
Of course I wanna see you.

15:49.449 --> 15:50.959
[ sighs ]

15:51.033 --> 15:53.613
You had so much promise,
could have been something,

15:53.703 --> 15:55.453
could have had a scholarship,
gone to college.

15:55.580 --> 15:57.290
You should have been a man
I could be proud of.

15:57.415 --> 15:58.705
[ melancholy music ]

15:58.791 --> 16:01.711
You got out of jail.
You didn’t even call me.

16:01.794 --> 16:03.794
‐ I’m sorry.
‐ Are you?

16:03.880 --> 16:06.600
Yes, Mom, I’m sorry.
Yes, you were right, okay?

16:06.674 --> 16:09.174
I was heading down
a path of sin.

16:09.302 --> 16:11.762
But, Mom, I was young,
and I was stupid,

16:11.846 --> 16:13.806
and I made a lot of mistakes.

16:13.931 --> 16:17.511
Look, I wanted to call you
so many times, but...

16:17.643 --> 16:19.183
I was ashamed
of the man I’d become.

16:19.312 --> 16:20.892
<i>♪</i>

16:20.980 --> 16:22.640
The only reason
why I’m here today

16:22.732 --> 16:25.232
is ’cause I’m trying
to get on the right path.

16:25.318 --> 16:28.118
Mama, I’m changing everything.

16:28.196 --> 16:29.986
I wish I’d listened to you
when I was younger.

16:30.114 --> 16:31.534
<i>♪</i>

16:31.657 --> 16:35.707
I wish I did a lot
of things differently,

16:35.828 --> 16:37.208
so I’m sorry
I didn’t call you.

16:37.330 --> 16:39.210
<i>♪</i>

16:39.332 --> 16:42.122
Look, me and my girl,
we starting fresh.

16:42.210 --> 16:45.760
We gettin’ out of New York,
away from all the bad
influences, everything.

16:45.838 --> 16:47.258
‐ [ sighs ]
‐ I don’t want this anymore.
I don’t want‐‐

16:47.340 --> 16:49.180
Oh, Dre.

16:49.258 --> 16:52.058
<i>♪</i>

16:52.178 --> 16:54.348
I just need
a little bit of money

16:54.430 --> 16:56.840
to give my daughter a chance
at a good life somewhere safe.

16:56.974 --> 16:58.604
Daughter?

16:58.684 --> 17:01.354
So now you have a daughter?

17:01.437 --> 17:03.027
Yeah, Mama.

17:03.105 --> 17:05.985
I know. I know.
I messed up, okay? I’m sorry.

17:06.067 --> 17:09.027
I‐I‐I should have told you.
It was wrong.

17:09.111 --> 17:12.531
Proverbs 13.

17:12.657 --> 17:15.827
"A righteous man hateth lying,

17:15.910 --> 17:18.250
"but a wicked man is loathsome

17:18.371 --> 17:19.581
and cometh to shame."

17:19.705 --> 17:21.995
<i>♪</i>

17:22.083 --> 17:24.083
When you gonna stop lying,
Andre?

17:24.210 --> 17:26.050
Mama, I’m not lying.
I got‐I got‐‐

17:26.128 --> 17:27.838
You think you can come
back here after all this time

17:27.922 --> 17:29.922
and I’m just gonna
give you money

17:30.049 --> 17:34.059
’cause you made up a story
about making a better life
for some daughter I never met?

17:34.178 --> 17:36.438
You think you can
play me like that?

17:36.556 --> 17:38.436
I fell for too many
of your lies.

17:38.558 --> 17:39.688
Never again.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.602
Mama!

17:44.730 --> 17:47.850
<i>♪</i>

17:52.572 --> 17:53.942
Ain’t there supposed to be
little babies running around

17:54.073 --> 17:55.243
this shit or something?

17:55.324 --> 17:57.154
Just get the fuck
out of here, Dre,

17:57.243 --> 17:58.913
’cause whatever you selling,
I ain’t buying.

17:59.036 --> 18:01.666
But I got something
that you might want:

18:01.747 --> 18:03.797
your son’s future.

18:03.916 --> 18:06.756
You see, I know Tariq’s been
dealing some serious weight,

18:06.877 --> 18:08.627
so if you don’t want me
to tell the cops,

18:08.754 --> 18:10.464
you gonna have to pay me
to forget what I know.

18:10.590 --> 18:12.260
What?
You think I’m stupid?

18:12.341 --> 18:15.051
The only way you know anything
about what Tariq is doing

18:15.136 --> 18:17.136
is ’cause you gave him
the brick, right?

18:18.764 --> 18:22.394
So you can’t say shit
to law enforcement,

18:22.476 --> 18:24.106
because then they might start
asking you questions

18:24.228 --> 18:26.818
about where you got the drugs
from in the first place.

18:26.939 --> 18:29.779
I got that brick
from your husband,

18:29.900 --> 18:31.860
so if you want you and me
to be the only ones

18:31.944 --> 18:34.824
who know about young Tariq’s
little "business expansion,"

18:34.947 --> 18:37.327
you gotta give me
50,000 reasons

18:37.450 --> 18:39.160
to keep it that way.

18:39.285 --> 18:40.785
[ scoffs ]

18:42.747 --> 18:47.257
Do you not see
this empty room?

18:47.335 --> 18:50.085
I put all my money down
to get this place going,

18:50.171 --> 18:51.961
and I ain’t got no customers.

18:52.048 --> 18:53.508
Parents took their kids
out of here

18:53.633 --> 18:54.463
because the cops came through.

18:54.550 --> 18:56.340
I don’t give a fuck.

18:56.469 --> 18:57.809
That ain’t my problem.

18:57.887 --> 18:59.727
Well, broke is broke, nigga.

18:59.805 --> 19:02.015
You get my money

19:02.141 --> 19:04.971
or my brick this morning,

19:05.102 --> 19:07.722
or I’ll burn
this whole motherfucker
down to the ground,

19:07.813 --> 19:09.183
and you’ll have less
than nothing.

19:09.315 --> 19:11.065
So call your son.

19:11.150 --> 19:13.480
He’s a resourceful
little nigga.

19:13.569 --> 19:14.489
He’ll get it done.

19:14.570 --> 19:17.440
[ dark music ]

19:17.531 --> 19:18.991
<i>♪</i>

19:19.075 --> 19:20.495
Tell him we need to meet.

19:20.618 --> 19:23.128
<i>♪</i>

19:30.878 --> 19:32.338
Got my money?

19:32.421 --> 19:35.251
<i>♪</i>

19:46.185 --> 19:48.685
Hey, bro, that brick was worth
about 20 bands, man.

19:48.771 --> 19:50.021
This look like half that.

19:50.106 --> 19:52.606
Short notice, all right?
I got what I could.

19:52.692 --> 19:54.232
You know I’m good
for the rest of it,

19:54.360 --> 19:56.330
or else you wouldn’t
have given it to me
in the first place.

19:56.404 --> 19:58.234
We good?

19:58.364 --> 19:59.444
What choice I got?

19:59.532 --> 20:00.862
Look, I’ll give you
the rest of the money

20:00.991 --> 20:02.281
at the end of the week,
plus a fat bonus,

20:02.368 --> 20:04.118
if you could do
something else for me.

20:04.203 --> 20:05.033
[ scoffs ]

20:05.162 --> 20:07.242
So I gotta do
more shit for you.

20:07.373 --> 20:08.703
What now, man?

20:08.833 --> 20:11.123
I need a piece.
Untraceable.

20:12.670 --> 20:13.880
Who you trying to shoot?

20:14.004 --> 20:15.464
Now, why the fuck
would I tell you?

20:15.548 --> 20:17.178
’Cause I’m not looking
to help you and get charged

20:17.258 --> 20:20.098
as an accessory to murder
when you get caught.

20:21.721 --> 20:23.881
I just need it
for protection, man.

20:24.014 --> 20:25.804
And plus, if I had to use,
don’t worry.

20:25.891 --> 20:27.051
I ain’t gonna get caught.

20:27.143 --> 20:28.473
I ain’t playing
about the piece, man.

20:28.561 --> 20:30.351
Could you get me one
or not?

20:31.397 --> 20:33.737
You out of all people
should know this, youngblood.

20:33.858 --> 20:35.068
Ain’t shit in life free.

20:35.151 --> 20:36.691
And I told you I’d get you
the money, a’ight?

20:36.777 --> 20:37.987
I need this.

20:39.739 --> 20:41.079
[ sighs ]

20:42.533 --> 20:44.993
You want the piece,

20:45.077 --> 20:47.207
you give me what I need:

20:47.288 --> 20:49.288
access to someone
only you can get.

20:49.415 --> 20:50.705
Man, you don’t understand,
a’ight?

20:50.791 --> 20:52.331
Me and Ghost,

20:52.418 --> 20:53.968
we’re not fucking
with each other no more.

20:54.086 --> 20:55.426
And on top of that, I think
he’ll shoot you on sight.

20:55.504 --> 20:57.504
Mm‐mm, not if I go with you,
and honestly,

20:57.590 --> 20:59.930
I don’t give a fuck about
your little daddy issues.

21:00.009 --> 21:02.719
You want the piece?
That’s the price.

21:02.803 --> 21:04.683
[ door beeps ]

21:04.764 --> 21:07.644
<i>♪</i>

21:09.268 --> 21:10.438
Why the fuck are you here?

21:10.561 --> 21:11.431
Son, why‐why would you bring

21:11.520 --> 21:13.100
an enemy here, our enemy?

21:13.230 --> 21:14.690
Don’t you mean why am I not
on Riker’s Island right now?

21:14.774 --> 21:16.604
<i>TARIQ:
He knows about everything
</i> <i>I’ve done, Dad.</i>

21:16.734 --> 21:19.154
He threatened to talk
if I didn’t bring him here,
so I had no choice.

21:19.278 --> 21:21.948
<i>♪</i>

21:22.031 --> 21:23.821
Tariq, wait for your
little friend in the hallway.

21:23.949 --> 21:26.869
<i>♪</i>

21:26.952 --> 21:28.282
Close the door, son.

21:28.412 --> 21:30.832
<i>♪</i>

21:30.956 --> 21:32.126
[ door clicks shut ]

21:32.249 --> 21:33.299
What the fuck do you want, Dre?

21:33.375 --> 21:35.165
First of all, take that bass
out your voice,

21:35.294 --> 21:37.084
’cause I know
you ain’t gonna shoot me
with Tariq in the building.

21:37.171 --> 21:39.501
You got 30 seconds.
Go.

21:39.632 --> 21:41.462
I know you tried to frame me
for Jason’s murder.

21:41.550 --> 21:43.960
I got out of there
before the cops got to me.

21:44.053 --> 21:45.633
But I know you killed him.

21:45.721 --> 21:47.631
Jason’s dead?

21:47.723 --> 21:49.303
I had no idea.

21:49.391 --> 21:51.221
I just don’t know
how you did it.

21:51.310 --> 21:53.890
You got the Serbians thinking
I killed him too.

21:53.979 --> 21:56.149
They shot my shit up,
killed all my <i>primeras.</i>

21:56.232 --> 21:58.652
‐ Sounds like a "you" problem.
‐ Nigga, I’m a "you" problem.

21:58.776 --> 22:00.526
I know shit about you
and your son,

22:00.653 --> 22:03.573
and thanks to you,
I gotta get the fuck
out of town, man.

22:03.656 --> 22:06.076
I need money, Ghost,
and that’s where you come in.

22:06.158 --> 22:08.498
You pay me,
I disappear.

22:08.619 --> 22:12.129
You don’t pay me,
I go straight to the Feds
and not just about you...

22:12.206 --> 22:13.666
about your
little baby boy too.

22:13.749 --> 22:16.169
[ growls ]

22:16.293 --> 22:18.213
‐ 250 bands.
‐ Man, fuck that.

22:18.337 --> 22:19.837
You ain’t gonna lowball me
with your son’s life
in the balance.

22:19.964 --> 22:21.964
That’s what I got on hand,

22:22.049 --> 22:23.219
and I have to go to get it.

22:23.342 --> 22:25.342
<i>♪</i>

22:25.469 --> 22:26.769
Okay.

22:26.846 --> 22:30.016
<i>♪</i>

22:30.099 --> 22:32.359
Well, go get it.
I’ll be right here.

